last_episode_to_air.name: In Dreams Begin Responsibilities
last_episode_to_air.overview: Jordan asks Brian for help on winning back Angela's affections; Sharon and Rayanne reach a turning point in their relationship; and Rickie learns that the new girl has a crush on him.

name: My So-Called Life
overview: The life of a 15 year-old high school student, whose angst-ridden journey through adolescence, friendship, parents, and life teaches her what it means to grow up.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: A 15-year-old girl and her trials and tribulations of being a teenager and dealing with friends, guys, parents and school.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: Welcome to the world of Angela Chase. At 15, Angela is sick of her goody goody look, and act. So she decides to hang out with the rebel herself Rayanne Graff, and dyes her hair Crimson Glow. Her mother is not pleased with the new Angela, and states that quite a few times, in this pilot. Her father on the other hand doesn't see the deal.

episodes.name: Dancing in the Dark
episodes.overview: While Angela awkwardly tries to get closer to Jordan, Graham and Patty learn to romance each other again.

episodes.name: Guns and Gossip
episodes.overview: There is gossip among this school.

episodes.name: Father Figures
episodes.overview: In multi-generational father-daughter conflict, Patty must take control of the printing business from her father, and Angela approaches Graham for the first time as a person rather than a superhero.

episodes.name: The Zit
episodes.overview: Angela and Patty come to grips with the feeling that they are not measuring up to some standard of beauty as Angela breaks out and Patty develops laugh lines.

episodes.name: The Substitute
episodes.overview: Liberty High deals with the issue of censorship when a substitute English teacher encourages students to write liberal poetry for the school paper.

episodes.name: Why Jordan Can't Read
episodes.overview: Angela makes a real connection with Jordan when she discovers that he has difficulty reading.

episodes.name: Strangers in the House
episodes.overview: Sharon's dad has a heart attack that causes Graham to question his own mortality and puts stress on his marriage while the event mends the broken friendship between Sharon and Angela.

episodes.name: Halloween
episodes.overview: Angela finds herself in 1963 during a mystical Halloween experience; Graham and Patty create some magic of their own with the help of medieval Halloween costumes.

episodes.name: Other People's Mothers
episodes.overview: Patty gains strides in her relationship with Angela when she helps Rayanne during an overdose.

episodes.name: Life of Brian
episodes.overview: Brian's life is a constant struggle over what he wants to express and the ramblings that escape from his mouth; everyone feels like the outsider at the ""World Happiness Dance"" at school; Patty pressures Graham into taking a continuing education cooking class.

episodes.name: Self-Esteem
episodes.overview: Self-esteem is the lesson of the day for Angela's warped relationship with Jordan, Brian's unreciprocated devotion to Angela, Rickie's flair for the dramatic, and Graham's cooking expertise.

episodes.name: Pressure
episodes.overview: Angela must make the decision whether or not to sleep with Jordan, while Graham is being pressured into going into the restaurant business with Hallie Lowenthal.

episodes.name: On the Wagon
episodes.overview: Rayanne has been sober for 33 days. To start getting her life back together again and to spend more time with Angela, she joins Jordan's band. But after a case of stage fright and a glimpse at what being sober really means, she goes back to the bottle.

episodes.name: So-Called Angels
episodes.overview: The Chase's Christmas is more complicated than usual when Angela's anxious search for Rickie leads her into the world of runaway kids where she encounters a mysterious homeless girl.

episodes.name: Resolutions
episodes.overview: It's New Year's Eve and while everyone else is busy making or breaking his or her resolutions, Rickie faces an increasingly difficult situation.

episodes.name: Betrayal
episodes.overview: Angela realizes she is over Jordan and is in to someone else. But Brian Cracow catches Rayanne and Jordan on tape having sex.

episodes.name: Weekend
episodes.overview: On a romantic weekend getaway to ""reconnect"" with Graham, Patty reveals another side of her personality; Angela copes with a visit from Rayanne, who has good reason not to leave.

episodes.name: In Dreams Begin Responsibilities
episodes.overview: Jordan asks Brian for help on winning back Angela's affections; Sharon and Rayanne reach a turning point in their relationship; and Rickie learns that the new girl has a crush on him.
